    {
      "id": "8ff8d4f1-2c6c-4a19-9b62-2cc38ba67328",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $n$ un entier naturel supérieur ou égal à $2$. Pour $k\\in\\Zz$, on pose $\\omega_k=e^{2ik\\pi/n}$.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> un entier naturel\nsupérieur ou égal à <span class=\"math inline\">\\(2\\)</span>. Pour <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(k\\in\\Zz\\)</span>, on pose <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\omega_k=e^{2ik\\pi/n}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "80e7893d-2d8f-4580-9445-38644cc74dab",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Calculer $\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}\\left(1+\\frac{2}{2-\\omega_k}\\right)$.",
        "html": "<p>Calculer <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}\\left(1+\\frac{2}{2-\\omega_k}\\right)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c7466945-8dea-4603-97a1-dae5e7727ea5",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(1+\\frac{2}{2-\\omega_k})=\\frac{\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(4-\\omega_k)}{\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(2-\\omega_k)}\n=\\frac{P(4)}{P(2)}=\\frac{4^n-1}{2^n-1}=2^n+1$.",
        "html": "<p><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(1+\\frac{2}{2-\\omega_k})=\\frac{\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(4-\\omega_k)}{\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(2-\\omega_k)}\n=\\frac{P(4)}{P(2)}=\\frac{4^n-1}{2^n-1}=2^n+1\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "76833d83-9364-45da-a70c-7a50c01aba43",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que, pour tout réel $a$, $\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(\\omega_k^2-2\\omega_k\\cos a+1)=2(1-\\cos(na))$ (questions indépendantes.)",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que, pour tout réel <span class=\"math inline\">\\(a\\)</span>,\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(\\omega_k^2-2\\omega_k\\cos\na+1)=2(1-\\cos(na))\\)</span> (questions indépendantes.)</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "7b76f533-1a0f-408d-828e-ec4273b1054d",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$$\\begin{align*}\\ensuremath\n\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(\\omega_k^2-2\\omega_k\\cos a+1)&=\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(e^{ia}-\\omega_k)(e^{-ia}-\\omega_k)=P(e^{ia})P(e^{-ia})=(e^{ina}-1)(e^{-ina}-1)\\\\\n &=2-e^{ina}-e^{-ina}=2(1-\\cos na).\n\\end{align*}$$",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[\\begin{align*}\\ensuremath\n\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(\\omega_k^2-2\\omega_k\\cos\na+1)&amp;=\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(e^{ia}-\\omega_k)(e^{-ia}-\\omega_k)=P(e^{ia})P(e^{-ia})=(e^{ina}-1)(e^{-ina}-1)\\\\\n&amp;=2-e^{ina}-e^{-ina}=2(1-\\cos na).\n\\end{align*}\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    }
  ],
